{"id":13848,"title":"Methocarbamol suspension for the treatment of rhabdomyolysis in equines.","abstract":"Rhabdomyolysis in equines occurs in horses due to physical overexertion or underlying pathologic myopathy. Methocarbamol is a muscle relaxant that can be used in equines to treat symptoms associated with Rhabdomyolysis. Methocarbamol is available as a solution for injection but is not commercially available as an oral suspension. This article focuses on the treatment of Tying-up caused by overexertion, and details the treatment of Rhabdomyolysis with an oral suspension that was prepared for a veterinarian by a compounding pharmacist.","date":"2014-01-27","categories":"Animal Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24459784","annotations":[{"name":"Pathology","weight":0.846685,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathology"},{"name":"Injection (medicine)","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injection_(medicine)"},{"name":"Veterinarian","weight":0.72699,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veterinarian"},{"name":"Pharmacist","weight":0.706736,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacist"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.699927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Muscle","weight":0.675547,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.667165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Mouth","weight":0.470534,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouth"},{"name":"Rhabdomyolysis","weight":0.353049,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhabdomyolysis"},{"name":"Horse","weight":0.21715,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horse"},{"name":"Muscle relaxant","weight":0.209485,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle_relaxant"},{"name":"Myopathy","weight":0.0932836,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myopathy"}